@node introduction "Introduction"

Some times the install utilities for programs replace some system files
(eg. in Libs or Devs directory) for older. Other progs need newer files
and not starting. Only way out is good  -  make backup of system files.
You say: there so many similar programs.  But I say:  Only  my  MuckIt!
make it so easy and fast (if you have a good configuration 8-).
@endnode

@node Requierements "Requierements"

   MuckIt! requierements:
        - OS2.1+
        - Lzx in C: directory (not included)
        - reqtools.library in Libs:
   Recomended:
        - hard drive
        - lots of mem (faster)
@endnode

@node Installation "Installation"

  Just copy the files:
        MuckIt!
        MuckIt!.guide
  in to any directory

  and:
        Env:MuckIt!.prefs  (see @{" Configuration " link configuration})
  to Env:

@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"

     MuckIt! use a Lzx program with syntax:
     C:Lzx -e -r -9 a <Archive> <Dir/Files>
(In this version lzx syntax may not be changed!)

When you run MuckIt! you see the window with some buttons  named, eg.:
Devs, Classes, Libs. When you mark this buttons, and put the "MuckIt!"
button (botom of the window), the drawers in Sys: will be packed using
lzx archiver and placed in destination directory (see @{" Configuration " link configuration}).

That's all!

To quit just click on the close gadget.
@endnode

@node configuration "Configuration"

Configuration is simple. Just edit Env:MuckIt!.prefs. In this file
is destination path for lzx archives. Change this entry, eg.:
        Ram:       for     Ram:Archive.lzx
        Hd1:Pack/  for     Hd1:Pack/Archive.lzx
        Trash:Lzx/ for     Trash:Lzx/Archive.lzx

If MuckIt! not found MuckIt!.prefs default path is Ram:
@endnode

